definition: class/rank/grade/equal to/same as/to wait for/to await/et cetera/and so on/et al. (and other authors)/after/as soon as/once

sentences.english: Omega equals 2pi times the spin frequency.
Twelve inches go to one foot.
Well, if you look at all these hyperbola's, xy equals constant.
sentences.chinese: 如果你們看這裏所有的雙曲線的話，xy等於常數。

sentences.english: Humidity has a huge role. As we sweat we bring liquid to the surface of our skin.
sentences.chinese: 溼度是一個很大的原因，因排汗等於將水分帶到體表。

sentences.english: You lean upon a broken reed, if you trust to their compassion.
sentences.chinese: 你若是指望他們的同情，那你就等於倚在破葦杆上。

sentences.english: Do not meet does not mean not miss, do not contact just to cover up nostalgic.
sentences.chinese: 䇓翱不見面不等於不思念，不聯絡只是爲了掩飾眷戀。

sentences.english: Thus, all inter-packet intervals are the same and equal to the fixed value.
sentences.chinese: 這樣可使得所有時延間隔相同且等於該固定值。

sentences.english: If A is a success in life, then A equals x plus y plus z.
sentences.chinese: 若A爲人生中的一項成就，那麼A就等於X加Y加Z。

sentences.english: MU( 1) is a class of minimal unsatisfiable formulas with the deficiency of the number of clauses and variables to be one.
sentences.chinese: 是子句數與變元數的差等於1的極小不可滿足公式類。

sentences.english: So disproving it's her pancreas proves it's her brain?
sentences.chinese: 所以排除了胰腺問題等於證明了大腦問題？

sentences.english: I know I'll set a fox to keep the geese if I take him for a good friend.
sentences.chinese: 我知道要是把他當好朋友的話，等於引狼入室了。

sentences.english: What we see here does not add up to traditional Corded Ware cultural norms.
sentences.chinese: 我們在這所看到的並不等於傳統的有線窯文化規範。

sentences.english: A city that parleys is half gotten.
sentences.chinese: 與敵人談判的城市，等於一半被佔領。

sentences.english: So it's the same as q reversible plus w reversible.
sentences.chinese: 它們是相等的，因此這也等於q可逆加w可逆。

definition: as for/as to/to go so far as to
to ask for trouble/to invite difficulties
lit. chasing the wind and clutching at shadows (idiom); fig. groundless accusations/to act on hearsay evidence
to argue strenuously or with sophistry/to quibble
to consider past cause and future effect (idiom); to think over the past and future/to ponder over reasons and connection
see 拔苗助長|拔苗助长[ba2 miao2 zhu4 zhang3]
to tolerate is to nurture an evildoer (idiom); spare the rod and spoil the child
